variable defined: TEST_SYSTEM=slim

import
com.sefaira.common

You can use these tests to verify that the values of environment variables are being successfully plugged into src/main/resources/application.conf.
E.g. The first two tests verify that the values of the following properties are foo and bar respectively:

fitnesse {
wiki-pages {
git-repository = ${?FITNESSE_WIKI_PAGES_GIT_REPOSITORY}
git-branch = ${?FITNESSE_WIKI_PAGES_GIT_BRANCH}
}
}

If the indicated environment variables are defined and have the right value, then the configuration parameters that refer to the variables will have the expected values and the tests will pass.
Otherwise (the environment variables are not defined or have the wrong value) the tests will fail.
So to get the first two tests to pass you have to define the two environment variables and give them the indicated values:

export FITNESSE_WIKI_PAGES_GIT_REPOSITORY=foo
export FITNESSE_WIKI_PAGES_GIT_BRANCH=bar
